column5: Typical weekend on my pond.  #1 always a bit of open water on the way out ,, no biggy,, maybe a foot at best.  #2&3 the accomodations,, sausages make an outing   #4&5 always count on a few of these guys on any given day   #6 who invited this thing?   anybody lost a size 10 sandal ,,, with legs?
That's a big water beatle !!!!!  Great fishing as well... and cooking ! Reminds me to find a small pan for fresh fillets... to go with my water boiling kettle for Mr. Noodles.
jesus wayne ...you wer'nt kidding about the van lines...
Yep, giant water beetle it is.  They can get massive.  Nice pike  Joey
nice jacks and that is a HUGE water beetle....nice report....

..water BUG. It's not a Coleoptera (beetle), its Hemiptera...the "true bugs". LoL  Might be a "Giant Water Bug" or one of the "Toe Biters"  Anyway. Nice little report. I love eating on the ice like that and the fish are always a bonus.  You should set up a photobucket account for you're photos. Easy and it presents them a little nicer.  Again, nice outing.  -Dave
cool on the fishin, and yepper those bugs can get pretty big, had one in the summer the kids where playing with, pretty wierd to see in the winter
great lookin day Bob! a few rockets and sausage! hope ya had at least one beer to wash them down with!
Hey,,fishing in style!!  Nice report!!  also funny what people see coming up their holes to take a look around!!
Great way to spend the day, anytime. Looks rather inviting .  Side note, There were only four beatles, George, Ringo, John and Paul.
Toe biter .. ouch...  nice bug too!
Nice set up there Waterwolf!  That's a great way to get even more enjoyment out of an outing on the lake.  Wtg.
Nice set up you got there WW.  PMSL @ size 10 sandle...good one...too funny.  Nice pike too BTW   Thanks for sharing  Simon
Great report and pics Waterwolf  Ya should of kept the bug.... ya could of used it for jigging  Nice looking set of gators for sure Thanks for sharing Leechman
